               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1211" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1211" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1211" type="surname" value="RIDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1211" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>BENJAMIN RIDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in partnership with my father—we live in South<lb></lb>wark. The prisoner was about five weeks in our employ—on the 29th of May I missed some hat leathers—I went to the prisoner's house in consequence of suspicion, and saw a female who I believe was his wife, on the 30th of May, and purchased of her three hat leathers, out of about eight dozen, which she produced—the prisoner had never bought any of us—I then informed my father, and went with a policeman and searched his house—I found three whole hat leathers in his parlour; and fifteen halves up stairs—I knew them to be ours by our stamping—we sell them in that states; but he never bought any—I have the machine that they were cut by, which enables me to know my own work—I only know it to be the prisoner's house in consequence of what his brother said—I never saw him there myself.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1212" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1212" type="surname" value="KERR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1212" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>ALEXANDER KERR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I searched the house which Mr. Rider took me to—I do not know it to be the prisoner's house—it was No. 11, Pitts-place—I never saw him there, or had any conversation with him about the property found there.</p>
